  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across 5 flow-speed combinations. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; required levels reflect MRL 5 stringency. The ContextOfUse prose references operating ranges (flow rates 3–7 L/min, rotational speeds 2400–3600 RPM) but no structured applicability constraint or operating envelope link is provided, leaving the formal boundary of valid model use unspecified.",
