      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software quality plan documented; version control, regression testing, and change control procedures in place and auditable.",
      "rationale": "Version control and regression testing are documented but the change control procedure lacks formal sign-off records for the hemolysis sub-model revisions introduced in solver v2.3. Achieved level falls one gradation below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests on canonical rotating-flow benchmarks confirm solver convergence rates match theoretical expectations to within 5%.",
      "rationale": "Taylor-Green vortex and lid-driven cavity benchmarks confirm second-order spatial accuracy. Rotating-frame Coriolis term verification is limited to a single RPM; multi-speed verification required at MRL 5 is incomplete."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent GCI analysis performed on all five operating points; GCI < 5% on hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Grid convergence study conducted at 3 of 5 operating points using three mesh densities (6 M, 12 M, 24 M cells). GCI on hemolysis index ranges 4–9%; two high-shear operating points exceed the 5% threshold, reducing achieved level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity profiles, fluid temperature, hematocrit) characterized with uncertainty bounds and matched to simulation inputs within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles measured by PIV; hematocrit and temperature recorded. However, fluid viscosity temperature dependence during extended test runs was not monitored continuously, introducing unquantified drift in blood analog properties."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., E_rms or validation uncertainty U_val) computed for hemolysis index and velocity field; metric meets pre-specified acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "E_rms on normalized hemolysis index is 18% across the five operating points; pre-specified threshold was 10%. Velocity field agreement is good (E_rms 6%) but the primary QoI threshold is not met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) directly correspond to the clinical decision QoIs; no surrogate substitution without documented justification.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is the primary clinical QoI and is directly validated. Shear stress distributions are used as an intermediate QoI; the power-law hemolysis model linking shear stress to hemolysis index introduces model-form uncertainty not fully propagated to the clinical threshold comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the FDA generic pump geometry at operating conditions spanning the COU flow-speed envelope; no significant geometric or operational extrapolation.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA generic centrifugal pump, matching the COU geometry. Operating points cover 3–7 L/min and 2400–3600 RPM as stated in prose, but the upper boundary (7 L/min, 3600 RPM) was tested in only one of two experimental campaigns, reducing spatial coverage confidence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated to residual levels at least three orders of magnitude below initial residuals for all operating points; mass and momentum imbalance reported.",
      "rationale": "Residuals drop four orders of magnitude for three operating points; two high-flow cases plateau at three orders of magnitude with minor oscillation in the hemolysis scalar transport equation, suggesting incomplete iterative convergence at peak loading."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by an independent analyst; checklist covering boundary condition assignment, turbulence model selection, and rotating reference frame configuration completed and archived.",
      "rationale": "Internal peer review was conducted but the reviewer was a co-developer of the hemolysis sub-model, limiting independence. An independent external review required at MRL 5 was not performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty for the power-law hemolysis model and turbulence closure quantified; sensitivity of hemolysis index to model form choices documented with uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Three turbulence models (k-omega SST, realizable k-epsilon, RSM) were compared; hemolysis index varies by up to 35% across closures at the highest shear operating point. No formal model form uncertainty quantification framework (e.g., Bayesian model averaging) was applied; the gap is substantial at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (blood viscosity, hemolysis model coefficients C and alpha) characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation performed with at least 500 samples.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with 1000 samples propagating uncertainty in viscosity, hemolysis coefficients, and inlet turbulence intensity. Distribution for hemolysis coefficient alpha is taken from a single literature source with limited sample size (n=12), underestimating epistemic uncertainty in that parameter."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental hemolysis measurements repeated across at least three independent test runs per operating point; inter-run variability reported and incorporated into validation uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Two of five operating points have three independent experimental repeats; the remaining three have only two repeats each. Inter-run coefficient of variation reaches 12% at the highest flow condition, and the limited repeat count prevents robust estimation of experimental uncertainty at those points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) demonstrated to be equivalent to COU device and operating conditions within documented tolerances; any deviations quantified.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump geometry is used in both simulation and experiment; dimensional inspection confirms geometric fidelity within 0.05 mm. Blood analog fluid properties match target hematocrit within 2%. Minor deviation in outlet pressure boundary condition specification (fixed pressure vs. measured waveform) is documented but its effect on hemolysis index is not quantified."
    }
